cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.NE 

The paper deals with unsupervised domain adaptation for object recognition, which is a problem in machine learning. The use of graph transduction games and iterative algorithms suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of deep features and object recognition benchmarks suggests that the paper is also likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also involves the assignment of class labels, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the use of game theory suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
